[i]Zagreus' Journey[/i] is a mod for Hades II that adds the original route Zagreus took through Tartarus, Asphodel, Elysium and the Temple of Styx in the first game to the sequel. Escape the Underworld as Melinoë, battle familiar foes and bosses using her unique abilities and weapons, meet Zagreus' old friends, and reconnect with your family's past.

Wonder what it plays like? Take a look at what Haelian and Boated think of the mod:

[url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SIVrJya47YQ][size=3]So, someone put Hades 1 in Hades 2 and it's amazing. | Haelian[/size][/url]
[youtube]SIVrJya47YQ[/youtube]

[url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HYf_z8IV4LE][size=3]They put Hades 1 in Hades 2 and it's PERFECT | Boated[/size][/url]
[youtube]HYf_z8IV4LE[/youtube]

After installing the mod, a Chaos Gate will appear in the Crossroads, which will allow you to experience Zagreus' journey through the Underworld as Melinoë. It is highly recommended that you complete the true ending of Hades before playing with this mod, as not all story events are included.

[img]https://i.imgur.com/ue6UDKs.png[/img]

In order to use this mod you [i]must[/i] have Hades installed on your system at all times when playing Hades II.

[i][size=3][b][quote]The mod will not work without a Hades installation![/quote][/b][/size][/i]
If you have Hades and Hades II installed in different parent folders, please refer to the [url=https://github.com/NikkelM/Hades-II-HadesBiomes/wiki/Configuration]Configuration[/url] wiki page for instructions on how to ensure the mod can discover your Hades installation. You must start the game once to generate the configuration file.

You [b]must[/b] uninstall your Hades mods by renaming or deleting the "Mods" folder and running "modimporter.exe" before installing this mod!
Additionally, this mod will very likely [b]not[/b] be compatible with most mods from Nexus, due to the different way they modify the game files. This is especially true for mods that require you to replace entire files. To ensure you don't run into issues, please do not use Hades II mods from Nexus when playing with [i]Zagreus' Journey[/i]. The mod is compatible with mods from Thunderstore.

[size=4][b]RECOMMENDED INSTALLATION METHOD[/b][/size]

You can install this mod just like any other Hades II mod available on [url=https://thunderstore.io/c/hades-ii/p/NikkelM/Zagreus_Journey/]Thunderstore[/url], the recommended mod manager is [url=https://thunderstore.io/c/hades-ii/p/ebkr/r2modman]r2modman[/url]. Install r2modman by using "Manual Download" on the linked page, and running the setup executable in the downloaded ".zip" file.

Afterwards, you can find [i]Zagreus' Journey[/i] on the "Online" tab in r2modman, or use "Install with Mod Manager" on the [url=https://thunderstore.io/c/hades-ii/p/NikkelM/Zagreus_Journey]mod's Thunderstore page[/url]. The mod manager will automatically install any other mods this mod needs to work correctly. Start the game through the mod manager to make sure mods are enabled - use the "Start Modded" button on the top left.

[size=4][b]General installation information[/b][/size]

Starting the game the first time with the mod enabled will install a number of files.
[quote]This may take some time depending on your hardware, and the game will display a black screen during this time.[/quote]You can follow along the installation progress in the console window that opens when playing the game modded.

If the mod was installed successfully, a popup will open in the Training Grounds to let you know.

This mod requires an additional 1GB of disk space.

If you have Hades and Hades II installed in different parent folders, such as through different storefronts (Steam/Epic Games/Microsoft Store/Game Pass), you will need to provide the path of your Hades installation in the mod's configuration file in your mod manager. Set the "hadesGameFolder" configuration option to the folder where Hades is installed (such as "C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\Hades" if installed through Steam, "C:\Program Files (x86)\Epic Games\Games\Hades" if installed through Epic Games, or "C:/Xbox/Hades" for Microsoft Store/Game Pass). Refer to the Configuration section below for more information on how to find the configuration file.

If you would like more information or experience any issues, please refer to the [url=https://github.com/NikkelM/Hades-II-HadesBiomes/wiki/Installation-&-Uninstallation]Installation[/url] wiki page.

[b]Before removing[/b] the mod from r2modman, you should first uninstall it through the "uninstall" configuration setting, to prevent any issues with leftover files. Only uninstall the mod while in the Crossroads to prevent issues.

[size=4][b]Manual Installation (NOT RECOMMENDED)[/b][/size]

Again, I [b]HEAVILY [/b]advise against this method, as the potential for mistakes is much larger than using the mod manager linked above and installing the mod directly through the [url=https://thunderstore.io/c/hades-ii/p/NikkelM/Zagreus_Journey/]Thunderstore[/url] page. I will NOT be providing support for issues with the mod not working if the manual installation method was used. Using the manual installation method, you are essentially emulating all of the steps that r2modman would do for you, but without the dependency installation and proper folder structuring.

1. Install the mod loader
Place the main Hell2Modding file [i](link below)[/i], called d3d12.dll, next to the game executable called Hades2.exe inside [code]Hades II\Ship\[/code]

2. Run the game once
The mod loader will automatically create the mod folder in the game directory:
[code]Hades II\Ship\ReturnOfModding\plugins\[/code]

3. Install this mod + dependencies
Extract each of the mods + dependencies into their own folders in the 'plugins'
directory. Each folder-name should have the structure 'Author-ModName' [i](note that capitalization is important!)[/i].


4. Run the game
If everything worked, you should see
[code][INFO/lua_module.cpp:150] Loading NikkelM-Zagreus_Journey-x.x.x
[INFO/lua_module.cpp:165] Loaded NikkelM-Zagreus_Journey-x.x.x
[/code]in the console in green, just before all the blue text.

